Pollutants for which air pollution alerts are to be issued under Article 8 (4) of the Act shall be the following pollutants, of the pollutants for which environmental standards are established under Article 12 of the Framework Act on Environmental Policy: <Amended on Jul. 20, 2012; Feb. 5, 2014; Feb. 8, 2019> 
1.	Fine dust (PM-10); 
2.	Ultrafine dust (PM-2.5); 
3.	Ozone (O3).

%MACHINE_TRANSLATED% Article 15 (1) Medical personnel or founders of medical institutions shall preserve medical records, etc. as referred to in Article 22 (2) of the Act for the periods specified in each of the following subparagraphs. Provided, That if necessary for continued treatment, such periods may be extended once within the limits of the respective periods specified below: <Amended on May 29, 2015; Oct. 6, 2016; Dec. 29, 2016>
1. Patient register: 5 years;
2. Medical records: 10 years;
3. Prescriptions: 2 years;
4. Surgical records: 10 years;
5. Test data and written findings: 5 years;
6. Radiographic images (including visual media) and written opinions: 5 years;
7. Nursing records: 5 years;
8. Midwifery records: 5 years;
9. Copies of medical certificates, etc. (to be preserved separately by type, such as medical certificates, death certificates, and postmortem examination reports): 3 years.

%MACHINE_TRANSLATED% Article 106 (2) Where an asset management company intends to merge investment trusts, it shall prepare a merger plan stating the following matters and obtain approval from the general meeting of beneficiaries of each investment trust subject to the merger: <Amended on Oct. 5, 2004>
1. The amount of the increased trust principal and the number of beneficiary certificates of the surviving investment trust resulting from the merger;
2. Matters concerning the allocation of beneficiary certificates to be issued to the beneficiaries of the dissolved investment trust;
3. Where cash is to be paid to the beneficiaries of the dissolved investment trust, the details thereof;
4. The date of the general meeting of beneficiaries of each investment trust to be merged;
5. The date on which the merger is to take place;
6. Where the trust deed of the surviving investment trust is to be amended due to the merger, the details thereof;
7. Other matters prescribed by Presidential Decree.

Any of the following persons shall be punished by imprisonment with labor for not more than three years or by a fine not exceeding 30 million won: <Amended on Aug. 4, 2005; Jun. 7, 2013; Jul. 20, 2015>
1.	Any person who has run the security business without obtaining a license therefor under Article 4 (1);
2.	Any person who has leaked confidential information that he or she has obtained while performing his or her duties or used such confidential information for unjust purposes, in violation of Article 7 (4);
3.	Any special security business entity or a security services agency that has failed to notify the suspension of its special security services or to take over immediately the special security services, in violation of Article 7 (8);
4.	Any person who has subcontracted the security services to a person who has failed to obtain the license referred to in Article 4 (1) when placing security guards at a collective petition site, in violation of Article 7-2 (1);
5.	Any person who has directly hired security guards when he or she places 20 or more security guards at a collective petition site, in violation of Article 7-2 (2);
6.	Any contractor who intervenes in, or exerts influence on, the hiring of an unqualified person, unsuitable person, etc. when a security business entity hires a security guard, in violation of Article 7-2 (3);
7.	Any special security guard who has mistakenly caused an impediment to the normal operation of a key national establishment, in violation of Article 14 (2);
8.	Any special security guard who has committed a violation of Article 15 (1) or (2) at the time when an emergency situation is caused by the grounds of the theft and damage of facilities and the explosion of hazardous substances in the guard area;
9.	Any person who has caused a security guard to commit an act deviating from the scope of the security services, in violation of Article 15-2 (2).

%MACHINE_TRANSLATED% Article 16 (2) Where the head of an organization who has borrowed weapons and ammunition pursuant to Article 16 of the Decree intends to issue or collect such weapons and ammunition to or from auxiliary police officers, the following requirements shall be observed: Provided, That the number of rounds of ammunition under subparagraph 2 may be increased or decreased, issuance or collection of weapons and ammunition may be suspended, and weapons and ammunition may be recalled and centrally managed, in accordance with instructions of the competent chief of the police station:
1. When weapons and ammunition are issued or collected, the issuance or collection details shall be recorded in the weapons and ammunition ledger;
2. Ammunition shall be issued within the limit of 15 rounds per rifle and 7 rounds per pistol, and in such cases, older ammunition (by production date) shall be issued first;
3. Weapons and ammunition issued to auxiliary police officers shall be cleaned at least once a week;
4. If a weapon requires repair, a repair request may be made to the competent chief of the police station, along with a list of such weapons and the relevant weapon management card.

%MACHINE_TRANSLATED% Article 185 Any person who falls under any of the following subparagraphs shall be punished by a fine not exceeding five million won: <Amended on Oct. 5, 2004; Jul. 19, 2007>
1. A person who establishes or amends trust deeds without submitting the report under the proviso to Article 29 (1) or Article 31 (1);
2. A person who makes a false or fraudulent report under the proviso to Article 29 (1) or Article 31 (1);
3. A person who fails to report the establishment details of an investment trust in violation of Article 29 (3) or who files a false report;
4. A person who violates Article 86 (3) or (4);
5. A person who transfers invested equity in violation of Article 144-14 (2);
6. A person who fails to report or makes a false report in violation of Article 144-16 (3) or (4);
7. A person who fails to file a report or makes a false report in violation of Article 144-17 (2);
8. A person who engages in business after being suspended under Article 57 (1) of the Securities and Exchange Act, as applied mutatis mutandis under Article 148;
9. A person who violates Article 175 (3) by transferring indirect investment securities to another person;
10. A person who delegates business in violation of Article 176 (1);
11. A person who violates Article 177.

Where a public housing project operator intends to obtain approval of a plan for a public housing project (hereinafter referred to as "project plan") pursuant to Article 35 (1) of the Act, he or she shall submit a written application accompanied by the following documents under the subparagraphs to the Minister of Land, Infrastructure and Transport:
1.	A plot plan for housing, appurtenant facilities, and welfare facilities;
2.	Design documents for housing zone construction works (applicable only to housing zone construction works executed before housing construction);
3.	Documents stating the location, lot number, category, area, details of ownership and rights other than ownership, and names (trade name in cases of a corporation) and addresses of the holders of ownership and rights other than ownership, of the land, etc. to be expropriated or used (applicable only to the case of expropriating or using land pursuant to Article 24 of the Housing Act);
4.	A report and drawings on the reversion of public facilities, etc. under Article 29 of the Act;
5.	Documents necessary for the consultation under Article 35 (6) of the Act;
6.	Other documents prescribed by Ministerial Decree of the Land, Infrastructure and Transport.

Where a public housing project operator intends to undergo a completion inspection pursuant to Article 31 (1) of the Act, he or she shall submit an application to the Minister of Land, Infrastructure and Transport accompanied by the following documents:
1.	A completion report;
2.	A floor plan according to actual measurements and plainmetric floor plan recognized by the head of a Si/Gun/Gu;
3.	A report on the size of land and a ground plan, by purpose of use;
4.	A report and drawings on the reversion of public facilities, etc. under Article 29 of the Act;
5.	A report on the size of area of the developed land by owner;
6.	An old and new land register comparison diagram.

%MACHINE_TRANSLATED% Article 44-2 (4) The Korea Forest Soil and Stone Association shall prepare and submit the following documents to the head of the Korea Forest Service by the end of February each year: <Amended on Mar. 11, 2025>
1. Business performance report and financial statement for the previous year;
2. Business plan and income and expenditure budget for the current year.

%MACHINE_TRANSLATED% Article 45 (1) In order to conduct investigations, inspections, or examinations under Article 37 (1) of the Act, the head of the Korea Forest Service, etc. may take the following actions against persons engaging in forest conversion, temporary use of mountainous districts, extraction of soil and stone (hereinafter referred to as "forest conversion, etc."), or restoration: <Amended on Aug. 22, 2012; Oct. 30, 2018>
1. Request for reports;
2. Request for submission of materials;
3. Access to the mountainous district;
4. Any other action deemed necessary by the head of the Korea Forest Service to prevent forest disasters or preserve the landscape of mountainous districts.

Any of the following persons shall be punished by imprisonment for not more than five year or by a fine not exceeding 30 million won: <Added on May 19, 2020>
1.	Any person who acquires or transfers a means of access in violation of Article 6 (3) 1;
2.	Any person who borrows or lends a means of access, or storing, delivering or distributing a means of access, in violation of Article 6 (3) 2 or 3;
3.	Any pledger or pledgee who violates Article 6 (3) 4;
4.	Any person who conducts arrangement, brokerage, advertisement, or solicitation while receiving, requesting, or promising in return, in violation of Article 6 (3) 5;
5.	A person who is provided with or provides information related to an account, or a person who keeps, conveys, or distributes an account, in violation of Article 6-3.

